comment:
* Mirrored Stream Classification Service (MSCS) parameters.
 * Refer to section 3.1 of the Wi-Fi QoS Management Specification v3.0.
 * @hide

variables.name: FRAME_CLASSIFIER_IP_VERSION
variables.comment: IP version used by the traffic stream

variables.name: FRAME_CLASSIFIER_SRC_IP_ADDR
variables.comment: Source IP address used by the traffic stream

variables.name: FRAME_CLASSIFIER_DST_IP_ADDR
variables.comment: Destination IP address used by the traffic stream

variables.name: FRAME_CLASSIFIER_SRC_PORT
variables.comment: Source port used by the traffic stream

variables.name: FRAME_CLASSIFIER_DST_PORT
variables.comment: Destination port used by the traffic stream

variables.name: FRAME_CLASSIFIER_DSCP
variables.comment: DSCP value used by the traffic stream

variables.name: FRAME_CLASSIFIER_PROTOCOL_NEXT_HDR
variables.comment: Indicates Protocol if using IPv4, or Next Header if using IPv6

variables.name: FRAME_CLASSIFIER_FLOW_LABEL
variables.comment: Flow label. Only applicable if using IPv6

methods.name: public int getFrameClassifierFields()
methods.comment:
* Get the frame classifier fields bitmap.
     * See {@link Builder#setFrameClassifierFields(int)}
     *
     * @return Bitmap of {@link FrameClassifierField} represented as an int.

methods.name: public int getUserPriorityBitmap()
public int getUserPriorityLimit()
public int getStreamTimeoutUs()
